Preconditions:
The method should take a TreeNode object as the root of the tree.
The method should take an integer value as the distance.
The tree should have at least one leaf node.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the number of good leaf node pairs in the tree.
The method should not modify the tree structure.
The method should consider only leaf nodes for counting pairs.
The method should consider only pairs of leaf nodes that are at a distance less than or equal to the given distance.